# Git commit after feature changes

**Rule:** After any **feature change** (or coherent set of changes), the changes **must be committed on git**.

- Use clear, descriptive commit messages (e.g. "Add groups API and Groups/GroupDetail screens" or "Fix PlaceDetail retry on error").
- Prefer one logical change per commit when practical; avoid large unrelated mixes.
- Do not leave implemented work uncommitted at the end of a feature or task.

This keeps the repository history meaningful and makes it easier to review, revert, or deploy specific changes.
